.TH "polyglot\-agents" "7" "" "Runtime Documentation" "Polyglot Devcontainers"
.SH NAME
polyglot\-agents \- operating guidance for coding agents in the
container
.SH PURPOSE
This page describes how an agent should behave inside
polyglot\-devcontainers.
.SH WHEN TO USE
Read this page before making changes or declaring work complete.
.SH PRIMARY COMMANDS
.IP
.EX
man polyglot
man polyglot\-task\-contract
task maintainer:pull
task maintainer:task -- ci
task image:discover
task image:pin -- --write
task image:verify
task ci
.EE
.SH WORKFLOW
Agent defaults:
.IP "1." 3
gather context from local runtime docs and the workspace
.IP "2." 3
pull and use the published maintainer container as the only valid agent
execution environment
.IP "3." 3
follow the task contract
.IP "4." 3
inspect artifacts when doing security or dependency work
.IP "5." 3
use \f[CR]task image:discover\f[R] before changing published image base
references
.IP "6." 3
use an explicit write step such as \f[CR]task image:pin -- --write\f[R]
.IP "7." 3
verify the published images with \f[CR]task image:verify\f[R]
.IP "8." 3
classify critical published-image findings as either \f[CR]repo-fixable\f[R]
or \f[CR]upstream residual\f[R]
.IP "9." 3
prefer the latest upstream-supported binary release for third-party tools
and do not self-build vendor tools only to suppress scanner output
.IP "10." 3
use the smallest change that solves the real problem
.SH OUTPUTS / ARTIFACTS
Agents should treat \f[CR].artifacts/scans/\f[R] as a first\-class
source of evidence.
Published image maintenance also writes evidence under:
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]base-image-report.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]base-image-report.md\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]image-security/\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]image-security/residual-risk.json\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]image-security/residual-risk.md\f[R]
